1. Prospective and retrospective designs allow for comprehensive analysis of system performance over time, aiding in effective redesign.
2. These designs enable comparison between past and future states, facilitating informed decisions during system redesign.
3. By incorporating data from both before and after changes, these methods enhance the understanding needed for successful system redesign.
4. The ability to study systems in various stages allows for identifying areas needing improvement, crucial for systematic redesign processes.